                48  ``BaseConstraint``                                          
                49  ==================                                          
                50                                                              
                51  .. class:: BaseConstraint(*, name,                          
            violation_error_message=None)                                       
                52                                                              
                53      Base class for all constraints. Subclasses must         
            implement                                                           
                54      ``constraint_sql()``, ``create_sql()``, ``remove_sql()``
            and                                                                 
                55      ``validate()`` methods.                                 
                56                                                              
                57      .. deprecated:: 5.0                                     
                58                                                              
                59          Support for passing positional arguments is         
            deprecated.                                                         
                60                                                              
                61  All constraints have the following parameters in common:    
                62                                                              
                63  ``name``                                                    
                64  --------                                                    
                65                                                              
                66  .. attribute:: BaseConstraint.name                          
                67                                                              
                68  The name of the constraint. You must always specify a unique
            name for the                                                        
                69  constraint.                                                 
                70                                                              
                71  ``violation_error_message``                                 
                72  ---------------------------                                 
                73                                                              
                74  .. attribute:: BaseConstraint.violation_error_message       
                75                                                              
                76  The error message used when ``ValidationError`` is raised   
            during                                                              
                77  :ref:`model validation <validating-objects>`. Defaults to   
                78  ``"Constraint “%(name)s” is violated."``.                   
                79                                                              
                80  ``validate()``                                              
                81  --------------                                              
                82                                                              
                83  .. method:: BaseConstraint.validate(model, instance,        
            exclude=None, using=DEFAULT_DB_ALIAS)                               
                84                                                              
                85  Validates that the constraint, defined on ``model``, is     
            respected on the                                                    
                86  ``instance``. This will do a query on the database to ensure
            that the                                                            
                87  constraint is respected. If fields in the ``exclude`` list  
            are needed to                                                       
                88  validate the constraint, the constraint is ignored.         
                89                                                              
                90  Raise a ``ValidationError`` if the constraint is violated.  
                91                                                              
                92  This method must be implemented by a subclass.              
                93                                                              
                94  ``CheckConstraint``                                         
                95  ===================                                         
                96                                                              
                97  .. class:: CheckConstraint(*, check, name,                  
            violation_error_message=None)                                       
                98                                                              
                99      Creates a check constraint in the database.             
               100                                                              
               101  ``check``                                                   
               102  ---------                                                   
               103                                                              
               104  .. attribute:: CheckConstraint.check                        
               105                                                              
               106  A :class:`Q` object or boolean                              
            :class:`~django.db.models.Expression` that                          
               107  specifies the check you want the constraint to enforce.     
               108                                                              
               109  For example, ``CheckConstraint(check=Q(age__gte=18),        
            name='age_gte_18')``                                                
               110  ensures the age field is never less than 18.                
               111                                                              
               112  .. admonition:: Oracle                                      
               113                                                              
               114      Checks with nullable fields on Oracle must include a    
            condition allowing for                                              
               115      ``NULL`` values in order for :meth:`validate()          
